reviews.text: We only visited the Harbor Restaurant for their morning buffet but came away satisfied each time. The food was generally fresh and tasted good. There was some variation day to day and enough selections that I didn't feel like I are the same thing everyday. The custom omelet chef was also very good. Some of their labeling was out of date or wrong so done check what you're getting.
Nice place. Food is good and the environment is good too. If we can sit next to the window, it will be perfect.

Delicious food, good environment for friends  to have a chatting. Highly appreciate that staff of this restaurant are very nice, polite and patient. Service manner is excellent.
However, vegetables are not enough, for those customers who like vegetables are not desirable, waffles are not soft.
So, it is highly recommended to introduce this restaurant to friends, colleagues to celebrate birthaday or memorable days and moments.

This has to be one of the best buffet in town.  Every dish is done to high quality.  Lots of crab dishes tonight n they are all superb, great selection of dessert also.  And the price is so low, only 500 compare to the usual 700.

result.name: Renaissance Hong Kong Harbour View Hotel

reviews.text:
Great hotel views and friendly staff. Quite conveniently located at the convention center but you’ll have to walk to Central or take the train to other location. 

We particular loved the view and the staffs here. They were very warm and friendly. We were upgraded and the room was lovely. We also have access to the lounge and it’s overly crowded.
Great location! Great views! Great service! Helpful staff! Comfortable bed! Great food! All in all a great Hong Kong experience!
Incredible service. Had an issue at booking and the front desk was able to fix the issue immediately. Plus incredible views from the room!
Great hotel and location... Club lounge gets busy in the afternoon but good selection of drinks and snacks... Hotel clean and friendly staff

If you're going to the convention center then it is hard to beat this hotel.  The harbor view rooms have an impressive view of the Hong Kong Harbor that I can't help but keep looking at.  I originally booked a Garden View room but was upgraded to this Harbor View room.  Unfortunately it was a very busy holiday weekend so all the suites were sold out so further upgrades were unavailable but they did at least try, so I appreciate that.  The room isn't very large and lacks a bit of landing space but suits a single business traveller fairly well.  Note that at least in my room there was no bathtub if that matters to you.  The A/C seems a bit finicky as there doesn't appear to be any automatic setting, but I think I've finally found a happy medium after three days of playing around with it.  The lounge is three stories tall with jaw dropping views of the harbor (see my first photo, the other harbor photos are from my room at different times of the day).  As the hotel was so busy the lounge was super crowded at breakfast and during evening cocktails, I gave up after about 10 minutes.  Breakfast in the restaurant is a free option for Marriott elite members and seemed to be pretty good with a broad range of options.  It's about a 5 minute walk to the closest metro station and there are tons of food options.  A pretty solid recommendation if you have business at the convention center.

result.name: 香港萬麗海景酒店

reviews.text: 自座尖餐👍👍食品價格合理

去咗食嘢(自助餐 dinner)，第二次去，總體很好😁，但也有進步空間🤔
食物方面，芝士焗龍蝦🍤都叫抵食，但係食三四個半隻(1.5~2隻)會幾飽下。面食🍲方面任夾餸，面都有四款。小菜同前菜少吃。海鮮太好，大部分不太新鮮。湯🥘同刺身都好味，但種類少。燒物普通，蝦🍤太黏殼，其他沒大問題。甜品🍰最好，幾多種類同好食
服務方面，侍應相當有禮😀。
環境乾淨企理。
價格💲偏$600/person
住宿方面……我無住🤣
呢間酒店餐廳可以話值，都可以話唔值。
要食蠔同龍蝦(仲要幾多下)先抵，請自行衡量，以下為照片以供參考。BTW大部分照片要打橫睇。

result.formatted_address: 4 Harbour Rd, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: The Harbourview

reviews.text:
Great location, friendly staff, clean rooms.

We stayed here for a couple of nights as a pit stop. Check in took a while as the check-in assistant had to find our booking in their paper filing system. We were guided to our room, which had a lovely view of the harbour. The room decor was dated.

Considering we only slept at the hotel and spent our days and evenings outside, our stay was a pleasant one. The location was great. Wan Chai MTR is a short walk, as are many cafes and a couple of grocery stores. Airport journey was approx. 25 minutes by taxi. Would stay here again for location and price.

Great location. 
Our family were in 3 rooms on the 21st floor, which is sold as the optimal floor. It was modern and clean. Rooms are small but great. No noise. The harbour view was exceptional from our one room on that side of the building, the other side was a view of a mouldy wall. The service was exceptional. We were allowed a very early check in and a late check out. 
The buffet breakfast was adequate, hot and cold items. It was very pleasant on 2 mornings but horrendous on one very busy morning ( due mostly to other guests). 
I suspect the other floors may need refurbishment. 
Would come here again.

Very nice landscape view, everything is excellent given its quite affordable in comparison to adjacent hotels. 
- Didn't try the hotel brunch.
- Bathroom is very clean but a bit small.
- they have the Nespresso machine, free of charge.
- No weird smell.

Great Hotel, it's only a few minutes away from Admiralty Station where you can get a train and bus to everywhere in Hong Kong. When traveling back to the airport you can just take the A11 bus, which stops right behind the hotel. The location is absolutely great. The room was very cozy, large and had a magnificent view of the Skyline over in Kowloon. The staff was very friendly, welcoming and professional at all times. Can't recommend it enough, especially for the price.
Easily go to this hotel by airport shuttle bus. I love the harbor view in my room, especially watching the laser−show at night . I appreciated the help of the friendly staffs.

reviews.text:
駅までの立地もよく、値段も一晩約6000円とリーズナブルでした。
部屋も綺麗で気にならないレベル。
お客さんは欧米の方が多かった印象。
2人部屋に3人で泊まったので、1人は簡易ベッドでした。
鉄パイプとベニヤ板の底板で構成された簡易ベッドは野戦病院みたいでテンション上がりました。

큰 호텔은 아니지만 가격 대비 시설은 괜찮은 편입니다. 전시장과 가까워 업무 보기 편해 대만족입니다. 전시장 입구까지 걸어서 5분이내 거리입니다. 편의점 등 상점거리는 10분~15분 정도 걸어야합니다.
와이파이 속도 좋고 직원들도 친절합니다.^^

優點：位置極佳（會展中心正對面），靠海那側有大片海景，冷氣夠冷，房間熱水夠大，房價實惠
缺點：房間小，地毯有點髒，隔音不太好，浴室超小

前台服務態度很好，餐廳種類雖然不多但是還算中規中矩喔，重點是價格實惠啊

result.adr_address: 香港灣仔港灣道4號灣景國際
result.formatted_address: 香港灣仔港灣道4號灣景國際
result.name: Harbour Restaurant

reviews.text: 全包$388.團購優惠，超值、抵食😋
地方舒服，人不會太多，午市自助餐食物質素高，價錢便宜
這間酒店的自助餐對喜歡吃蠔的朋友來說簡直就是超值

我於2019年4月10日 到灣景國際賓館吃自助午餐 。成人費用208， 長者費用198。 今天一個成人一個長者加一服務費是$40.60  ， 匯豐信用卡 有八折，減$81.20    。 今天我用匯豐信用卡找數 ，到最後價錢是$365.4     。 很抵食。
即使食到差不多兩點十五分，這裏的甜品， 各種的湯類， 布甸等等也是 熱辣辣的。
經遏裝修之後， 座位有很多私人空間， 今天， 約十二點半鐘，已經坐滿人呀， 與兩三年前相比，可說是有天淵之別。 食物種類很多，今天我最愛吃的是： 壽司飯，煎鱸魚， 芝士焗意粉， 芝士焗青口………… 可以說，他們放出來的東西，無論是甜品，小吃，冷盤，沙律亦都非常乾淨，好吃。
要講一句，就是這裏並沒有生蠔， 放出來的不算是貴價食物。
餐廳內擺設也很舒適，美觀。 但是灣景國際賓館的地下大堂，走廊的擺設，非常樸素。
價錢合理，地方唔錯，食物都正!

result.vicinity: 灣仔港灣道4號灣景國際
